<build_gate_finding verbatim="true">

FINDING bg-003 (HIGH, rule correctness.spec-compliance):
The bg-002 fix-round error-handling middleware (server/index.js:9-15) returns 400 unconditionally for any syntactically-invalid JSON body, WITHOUT checking the signature first, even though the signature is checkable at that point. Verified live: POST /webhook with body 'not valid json{{{' and a deliberately wrong (but correct-length, well-formed) X-Signature header returns status 400 {"error":"invalid_body"}, not 401 {"error":"invalid_signature"}. req.rawBody (populated by the verify callback in express.json(), which runs BEFORE JSON.parse is attempted) and the X-Signature header ARE both present and readable inside the error-handling middleware at the moment the SyntaxError is caught -- so a signature check there is technically possible but is not performed. This violates the spec's explicit invariant that the signature check runs first / unconditionally (goal: "sig check still runs first -- a bad body with a valid sig is 400, not 401"). The converse -- a bad/unparseable body with an INVALID sig must be 401, not 400 -- is broken for the malformed-JSON-syntax input class specifically, since Express's body-parser intercepts the SyntaxError before the /webhook route handler (where the real signature check lives) ever runs. Not covered by any current test: the existing malformed-JSON test uses a VALID signature over the malformed bytes, and the existing malformed-signature test uses valid JSON. Neither combination (malformed JSON + invalid signature) is tested.
FIX HINT (from BUILD_GATE, not binding): "In the error-handling middleware (server/index.js:9-15), before responding, compute the expected HMAC over req.rawBody (already populated by the verify callback) and compare against the X-Signature header exactly as the route handler does; if the signature is missing/malformed/mismatched, respond 401 {error:'invalid_signature'} instead of 400. Only fall through to 400 {error:'invalid_body'} when the signature over the raw (unparseable) bytes is valid. Add a test posting malformed JSON with a deliberately invalid X-Signature and asserting 401."

</build_gate_finding>

